cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SD, cs.HC

This paper deals with natural language processing tools and their application to detect disturbances in transcribed speech of schizophrenia inpatients. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with natural language processing. The paper also uses machine learning techniques to analyze the speech patterns, which makes cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves the use of AI (Artificial Intelligence) techniques to detect schizophrenia, which makes cs.AI another possible sub-category. The paper also deals with the analysis of speech patterns, which could fall under cs.SD (Sound and Music Computing). Finally, the paper's focus on detecting schizophrenia in patients through their speech patterns makes cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) another possible sub-category.
